# Pipeline-check suppressions for this repo's own workflows.
#
# Format: CHECK_ID:RESOURCE per line. Comments start with ``#``.
# Auto-discovery picks this file up at cwd; no flag needed.
#
# Most prior entries here became redundant once the catalog gained
# structural detection: ``actions/deploy-pages`` (docs.yml) marks
# Pages-only workflows that the artifact heuristic now skips, and a
# job-level ``AWS_ENDPOINT_URL`` pointing at localhost (LocalStack)
# now exempts the affected jobs from GHA-005 and GHA-014. Only the
# residual cases that the catalog can't see structurally remain.

# ── localstack-test.yml — HTML report uploads, not software builds ──
# The terraform-fixture job uploads HTML pipeline-check reports via
# ``actions/upload-artifact@``. The signing / SBOM / vuln-scan /
# SLSA-attest checks treat any upload-artifact use as a software
# release; there's no further structural signal to distinguish "test
# report" uploads from real builds, so we suppress per-resource here.
GHA-006:.github/workflows/localstack-test.yml
GHA-007:.github/workflows/localstack-test.yml
GHA-020:.github/workflows/localstack-test.yml
GHA-024:.github/workflows/localstack-test.yml
# The ``pip install -e .`` in the test setup installs the package
# being tested. The hash-locked install
