# ── release.yml — SLSA generator must be tag-pinned, not SHA ────────
# The SLSA generator is consumed as a reusable workflow that produces
# Sigstore-signed provenance. ``slsa-verifier`` validates the
# attestation by matching the trusted-builder ref against an allow-
# list of known SLSA generator semantic-version tags. A SHA pin
# produces an unrecognized ref and breaks every downstream
# verification call (the consumer-side ``slsa-verifier verify-
# artifact --source-uri ...`` documented in the README). This is the
# one place SHA-pinning is the wrong call.
GHA-025:.github/workflows/release.yml
